{"cursor":"6604","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\nA 'sight' is a device used to assist aligning or aim weapons, surveying\ninstruments, or other items by eye. Sights can be a simple set or system of\nmarkers that have to be aligned together as well as aligned with the target\n(referred to as an iron sights on firearms). [http://books.google.com/books-\n?id=7QkvhpRwqgoC&pg=PA185&dq=types+of+sights&hl=en&ei=EJ4LTs3FHMKcgQfHj9WSAg&sa-\n=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=10&ved=0CFYQ6AEwCTgK#v=onepage&q=types%20of%-\n20sights&f=false Gunsmithing: pistols & revolvers, By Patrick Sweeney, page\n185] They can also be optical devices that allow the user to see the image\nof an aligned aiming point in the same focus as the target. These include\ntelescopic sights and reflector (or \"''reflex''\") sights. There are also sights\nthat project an aiming point onto the target itself, such as laser sights.\n","linknr":199,"url":"Sight_(device)","recorded":1362574441,"links":35,"instances":["ballistics"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Firearm components","Optical devices","Artillery components"],"headings":["Simple sights","Optical sights","List of sights","See also","Notes","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/US_Navy_060314-N-4007G-049_A_Canadian_Sea_Cadet_look_through_the_sights_of_a_machine_gun_mounted_on_an_SH-60B_Seahawk_helicopter_assigned_to_Helicopter_Sea_Combat_Squadron_Two_one_%28HSC-21%29.jpg/220px-thumbnail.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/Visierlinie.jpg/220px-Visierlinie.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/13/Scope_of_M-91.JPEG/220px-Scope_of_M-91.JPEG","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/49/Mark_III_free_gun_reflector_sight_mk_9